Frequently Asked Questions

What does Sauce’s Commission-Free Delivery Service really mean? Is it truly commission-free, or is there a catch?

Yes, Sauce truly is commission-free — and no, there’s no catch. We charge a small flat fixed fee that doesn’t increase with the order size. This means that Sauce users will now pay a low flat fixed fee per delivery order, regardless of order size and regardless of distance up to five miles (and up to 20 miles in selected cities).

Plus: You’ll now be able to utilize several leading delivery couriers throughout the country. So you’ll no longer be at the mercy of a single provider. You’re protecting your margins while saying goodbye to paying 30% commission per delivery order!

With Sauce, can I receive orders from all the channels above?

Yes, and it’s fully automated, hands-free, synced with your Dashboard.

Whether ordering via traditional website ordering, social media, or google, Sauce has a quick and enjoyable ordering option for any type of customer out there.

Sauce helps restaurants convert direct orders up to 10X higher than before, simply due to the fact that ordering from Sauce can originate from website orders, Facebook messenger, instagram, google, and much more to come in the near future.

Sauce also captures the customer data for the restaurant for full ownership, while retargeting those customers directly for abandoned carts in order to win back lost revenue more than ever before.

In short, Sauce helps restaurants own and control their online ordering and customer relationships, while converting customers in social media and other channels to provide convenience and maximize orders.

Who are the drivers that Sauce partners with?

We partner with the national delivery companies, as well as local ones.

This way, restaurants are not at the mercy of just one provider, and can utilize a dispatch system with Sauce that always selects the most readily available driver, all commission-free!
